This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it proposes a novel architecture for artificial neural networks that incorporates the concept of time. Additionally, the paper reports experiments on solving the XOR problem and the MNIST digits recognition benchmark, which are common tasks in the field of neural computing. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a new approach to designing artificial neural networks that could potentially improve their performance. 

The sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possibility as the paper discusses a training algorithm for the proposed stigmergic neural network. 

The sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper proposes a new architecture for artificial neural networks that could potentially be used in control systems. 

Finally, the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics) is a possibility as the proposed stigmergic neural network could potentially be used in robotics applications.
